The paper deals with creating an agent that can understand natural language and act intelligently in text-described environments, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of language models and measuring agent performance, which are related to machine learning (ML) and computational linguistics (CL), making cs.LG and cs.IR likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper discusses the agent's mechanisms for handling tasks, which could be related to computer systems and control (cs.CC).
